#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/crates-and-modules.md:1
msgid "Crates & Modules"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/crates-and-modules.md:3
msgid "Use workspace dependencies (`workspace-deps`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/crates-and-modules.md:5
msgid ""
"Always declare shared dependencies in the workspace `[workspace."
"dependencies]` table and reference them with `.workspace = true` in member "
"crates."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/crates-and-modules.md:10
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"# In the workspace root Cargo.toml\n"
"[workspace.dependencies]\n"
"ostd = { version = \"0.17.0\", path = \"ostd\" }\n"
"bitflags = \"2.6\"\n"
"\n"
"# In a member crate's Cargo.toml\n"
"[dependencies]\n"
"ostd.workspace = true\n"
"bitflags.workspace = true\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/crates-and-modules.md:22
msgid "Add module-level documentation for major components (`module-docs`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/crates-and-modules.md:24
msgid ""
"A module file that serves as an important kernel component (e.g., subsystem "
"entry point, major data structure, driver) should begin with a `//!` comment "
"explaining:"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/crates-and-modules.md:28
msgid "What the module does"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/crates-and-modules.md:29
msgid "The key types it exposes"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/crates-and-modules.md:30
msgid "How it relates to neighboring modules"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/crates-and-modules.md:33
msgid ""
"//! Virtual memory area (VMA) management.\n"
"//!\n"
"//! This module defines [`VmMapping`] and associated types,\n"
"//! which represent contiguous regions of a process's virtual address "
"space.\n"
"//! VMAs are managed by the [`Vmar`] tree in the parent module.\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/crates-and-modules.md:40
msgid "Default to the narrowest visibility (`narrow-visibility`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/crates-and-modules.md:42
msgid ""
"Start private, then widen to `pub(super)`, `pub(crate)`, or `pub` only when "
"an actual external consumer requires it."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/crates-and-modules.md:47
msgid "// Good — restricted to the parent module\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/crates-and-modules.md:52
msgid "// ...\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/crates-and-modules.md:54
msgid "// Bad — unnecessarily wide\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/crates-and-modules.md:59
msgid ""
"Inside the `aster-kernel` crate, `pub(crate)` and `pub` are equivalent, as "
"the crate has no downstream consumers. Prefer the shorter `pub`."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/crates-and-modules.md:63
msgid ""
"See also: PR [\\#2951](https://github.com/asterinas/asterinas/pull/2951), "
"[\\#2605](https://github.com/asterinas/asterinas/"
"pull/2605#discussion_r2720506912), and [\\#3154](https://github.com/"
"asterinas/asterinas/pull/3154#discussion_r3100905375)."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/crates-and-modules.md:68
msgid "Qualify function calls with the parent module (`qualified-fn-imports`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/crates-and-modules.md:70
msgid ""
"When importing a free function or a static/constant from another module, "
"import the **parent module** and access the item through it (`module::"
"function()`, `module::CONSTANT`). Do not import free functions or statics "
"directly by name."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/crates-and-modules.md:76
msgid ""
"This convention is recommended by [_The Rust Programming Language_](https://"
"doc.rust-lang.org/book/ch07-04-bringing-paths-into-scope-with-the-use-"
"keyword.html) and followed by the Rust compiler codebase. It serves two "
"purposes:"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/crates-and-modules.md:81
msgid ""
"The call site makes it clear that an imported item is being used, not a "
"local one."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/crates-and-modules.md:84
msgid "The module name provides context that complements the item name."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/crates-and-modules.md:88
msgid "// Good — module-qualified function call\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/crates-and-modules.md:92
msgid "// Good — module-qualified static access\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/crates-and-modules.md:97
msgid "// Bad — bare function name; unclear origin at call site\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/crates-and-modules.md:102
msgid "// Bad — bare static name; could be mistaken for a local constant\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/crates-and-modules.md:109
msgid ""
"This guideline applies to **free functions and statics/constants**. Types, "
"traits, and enum variants should still be imported directly by name, "
"following the standard Rust convention."
msgstr ""
